1 that position at the pleasure of the governor. The state board may
2 elect other officers and committees as it considers appropriate.
3 (4) The actual and necessary per diem compensation and the
4 schedule for reimbursement of expenses for the public members of
5 the state board shall be is the same as is established annually by
6 the legislature for similar boards that are reimbursed from the
7 general fund. The compensation and reimbursement, executive
8 director and staff salaries, and all actual and necessary operating
9 expenses of the state board shall must be paid from the trust fund,
10 according to an authorization as provided in section 9.
11 Sec. 9. (1) The state board may authorize the disbursement of
12 available money from the trust fund, upon legislative
13 appropriations, for exclusively the following purposes , which that
14 are listed in the order of preference for expenditure:
15 (a) To fund a private nonprofit or public organization in the
16 development or operation of a prevention program if at least all of
17 the following conditions are met:
18 (i) The appropriate local council has reviewed and approved the
19 program. This subparagraph does not apply if a local council does
20 not exist for the geographic area to be served by the program.
21 (i) (ii) The organization demonstrates an ability to match,
22 through money or in-kind services, 50% of the amount of any trust
23 fund money received. The amount and types of in-kind services are
24 subject to the approval of the state board.
25 (ii) (iii) The organization demonstrates a willingness and
26 ability to provide program models and consultation to organizations
27 and communities regarding program development and maintenance.
28 (iii) (iv) Other conditions that the state board may deem
29 consider appropriate.
