1 (b) To fund local councils.prevention partners.
2 (c) To fund the state board created in section 3 for the
3 actual and necessary operating expenses that the state board incurs
4 in performing its duties.
5 (2) Authorizations for disbursement of trust fund money under
6 subsection (1)(c) shall must be kept at a minimum in furtherance of
7 the primary purpose of the trust fund, which is to disburse money
8 under subsection (1)(a) and (b) to encourage the direct provision
9 of services to prevent child abuse and neglect.
10 Sec. 10. (1) In making grants to a local council, prevention
11 partner, the state board shall consider the degree to which the
12 local council prevention partner meets the following criteria:
13 (a) Has as its primary purpose the development and
14 facilitation of a collaborative community prevention program in a
15 specific geographical area. The prevention program shall must
16 utilize trained volunteers and existing community resources
17 wherever practicable.
18 (b) Is administered by a board of directors composed of an
19 equal number of members from the following 2 groups:
20 (i) A representative from each of the following local agencies,
21 as far as practicable: the
22 (A) The county department of social services, the department
23 of public health, the department of mental health, the health and
24 human services.
25 (B) The probate court. , the
26 (C) The office of the prosecuting attorney. , a
27 (D) A local law enforcement agency. , a
28 (E) A school district. , and a
29 (F) A number of private, local agencies that provide treatment
